Usage:
  cape submission new <scenario> <language> <version> <github-handle> --mode <base|open> [--slug <name>]

Required Arguments:
  <scenario>          Benchmark name (must exist in scenarios/)
  <language>          Compiler/language name (letters/digits/hyphens only)
  <version>           Compiler version (e.g., 1.52.0.0 or 1.1.17)
  <github-handle>     Your GitHub handle (1-39 chars, alphanumeric and hyphens)
  --mode <base|open>  Evaluation mode (REQUIRED)
                      base: Prescribed algorithm (compiler comparison)
                      open: Any optimization (real-world competition)

Options:
  --slug <name>       Optional for open mode (e.g., 'memoized', 'unrolled', 'pfix')
                      Omit for generic/default implementation
                      Not allowed for base mode

Examples:
  # Base mode (prescribed algorithm for compiler comparison)
  cape submission new fibonacci Plinth 1.53.0 Unisay --mode base

  # Open mode with generic/default implementation (no slug)
  cape submission new fibonacci Aiken 1.1.17 KtorZ --mode open

  # Open mode with specific optimization variant
  cape submission new fibonacci Plutarch 1.11.1 SeungheonOh --mode open --slug memoized

Directory Naming:
  - Base mode: <language>_<version>_<github-handle>_base
  - Open mode (generic): <language>_<version>_<github-handle>_open
  - Open mode (with slug): <language>_<version>_<github-handle>_open_<slug>

Notes:
  - Scenario must exist in scenarios/<scenario>/
  - Mode is REQUIRED - must explicitly choose base or open
  - Slug is optional for open mode; use only for specific optimization variants
  - Base mode requires implementing the exact algorithm prescribed in the scenario
  - GitHub handle rules: 1-39 chars, alphanumeric and hyphens, cannot start/end with '-'
